<subSubSection id="A6BCB103E0F71AD1113AA571E5A69C3F" pageId="812" pageNumber="813" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="625EA3B56BEF939D9222CE2D1342A8C1" pageId="812" pageNumber="813">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="552F1D5E60E63D086A5695E130D96182" pageId="812" pageNumber="813">
This species is found east of the Rocky Mountains from southern Quebec (Larochelle 1975: 91) to northeastern North Dakota (Tinerella 2003: 637), south to southeastern Texas along the Rio Grande and southern South Carolina, west to western Texas and western Oklahoma [see Madge 1967: Fig. 137]. The records from Baja California (Horn 1894: 310), Arizona (Wickham 1898: 300; Snow 1907: 142, as 
<taxonomicName id="1DA4D47517513F4CCE5BAD3F24D0343C" baseAuthorityName="Chaudoir" baseAuthorityYear="1871" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Lebia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="812" pageNumber="813" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="majuscula">
<emphasis id="BB8569E281EB7806C77D7F9AC427B782" italics="true" pageId="812" pageNumber="813">Lebia majuscula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), New Mexico (Fall and Cockerell 1907: 159, 160 as 
<taxonomicName id="D4F1686A259598761A198890E35CF4B7" baseAuthorityName="Chaudoir" baseAuthorityYear="1871" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Lebia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="812" pageNumber="813" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="majuscula">
<emphasis id="5CA0EEA9BA94F6AF49B0013B6E1F9708" italics="true" pageId="812" pageNumber="813">Lebia majuscula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and 
<normalizedToken id="3540A5675BAAEC734A5DCDC4319608C3" originalValue="“Colorado”">&quot;Colorado&quot;</normalizedToken>
(Snow 1877: 17; Wickham 1902: 239) need confirmation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
